Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:07 a.m. in Manila.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  rose less than 0.1
percent to 5,161.68.  First Metro Investment Corp. (FMIC)  , a financial
services provider, climbed 2.3 percent to 67.50 pesos.  The
company said first-quarter profit more than doubled from a year
earlier to 979 million pesos ($23 million), a stock exchange
filing showed.  Pepsi-Cola Products Philippines Inc. (PIP)   advanced 4.9
percent to 2.79 pesos, bound for the steepest gain since April
13. The soda pop-makerâ€™s first-quarter profit jumped to 224.9
million pesos from 31.9 million pesos a year ago, a stock
